Dialogue: 10,0:00:33.92,0:00:37.93,NarrTop,,0,0,0,,The year is 1956. March.
Dialogue: 10,0:00:38.54,0:00:42.67,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Today as well, Yamamoto Shinichi \Npresses forward from Kansai Headquarters,
Dialogue: 10,0:00:42.67,0:00:45.54,Narrator,,0,0,0,,commanding the Battle for Osaka.
Dialogue: 10,0:00:46.10,0:00:48.84,Default,,0,0,0,,"Incense and candles are all you need!"
Dialogue: 10,0:00:48.84,0:00:52.32,Default,,0,0,0,,That slogan, coined last month, \Nis now chanted all across Kansai!
Dialogue: 10,0:00:52.32,0:00:53.85,Default,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 10,0:00:53.85,0:00:59.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Once Toda’s words sparked a wildfire \Nin the hearts of our Kansai comrades,
Dialogue: 10,0:00:59.13,0:01:01.25,Default,,0,0,0,,it became unstoppable.
Dialogue: 10,0:01:01.25,0:01:03.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Exactly!
Dialogue: 10,0:01:03.56,0:01:05.82,Default,,0,0,0,,How are things going in Sakai, Asada-san?
Dialogue: 10,0:01:06.40,0:01:09.50,Default,,0,0,0,,We're observing an enormous religious surge!
Dialogue: 10,0:01:09.50,0:01:15.05,Default,,0,0,0,,First, roundtable attendance exploded—and now people are also bringing their friends along.
Dialogue: 10,0:01:15.05,0:01:15.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Good.
Dialogue: 10,0:01:15.60,0:01:18.80,Default,,0,0,0,,We’ve shifted to conversion, \Nbut the roundtables are picking up too—
Dialogue: 10,0:01:18.80,0:01:22.33,Default,,0,0,0,,everyone’s saying, \N“You guys are so jolly, it’s irresistible!”
Dialogue: 10,0:01:22.73,0:01:28.09,Default,,0,0,0,,I see. We played our cards right \Nand pulled off a smooth opening.
Dialogue: 10,0:01:28.09,0:01:31.91,Default,,0,0,0,,But the real battle starts now. \NWe can’t afford to let our guard down!
Dialogue: 10,0:01:31.91,0:01:32.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Got it!
Dialogue: 10,0:01:32.83,0:01:37.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Keep up the pace and continue intensive personal and family guidance throughout March.
Dialogue: 10,0:01:37.89,0:01:41.23,Default,,0,0,0,,The fruit of our religious guidance efforts
Dialogue: 10,0:01:41.23,0:01:43.90,Default,,0,0,0,,will be revealed at the Osaka-Sakai Joint General Meeting
Dialogue: 10,0:01:43.90,0:01:46.03,Default,,0,0,0,,at Osaka Baseball Stadium on April 8th.
Dialogue: 10,0:01:46.57,0:01:51.13,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the first time that a baseball stadium will be used for the Kansai general meeting.
Dialogue: 10,0:01:51.13,0:01:56.01,Default,,0,0,0,,I want this general meeting to ignite an explosion that gives us the edge in the Battle for Kansai.
Dialogue: 10,0:01:56.01,0:01:57.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 10,0:01:57.39,0:01:58.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 10,0:01:59.41,0:02:02.35,Default,,0,0,0,,But that would require \Na great deal of preparation.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:02.35,0:02:05.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's all put our minds to work \Nto make it a great success!
Dialogue: 10,0:02:05.50,0:02:09.11,Default,,0,0,0,,I have to leave for Yame in Kyushu tomorrow,
Dialogue: 10,0:02:09.11,0:02:13.34,Default,,0,0,0,,but please take care of everything in my absence, Branch Chief Haruki.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:13.34,0:02:15.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes! Consider it done.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:16.68,0:02:19.14,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Despite his packed schedule, Shinichi—
Dialogue: 10,0:02:19.14,0:02:22.33,Narrator,,0,0,0,,now overseeing all of western Japan \Nfrom Osaka westward— {and Kinki}
Dialogue: 10,0:02:22.33,0:02:29.96,Narrator,,0,0,0,,carved out time to offer guidance in Kyushu \Nto secure a sweeping victory in the July battle.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:33.97,0:02:38.97,NarrTop,,0,0,0,,Wherever he went, Shinichi went out of his way \Nto uplift every single member he met,
Dialogue: 10,0:02:38.97,0:02:43.69,NarrTop,,0,0,0,,sparking a natural wave \Nof proselytizing among them.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:47.83,0:02:54.59,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Back in Osaka, Shinichi was once again \Nthrust into the thick of routinely fierce battles.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:54.59,0:02:59.95,Narrator,,0,0,0,,During this period, Shinichi’s early morning scripture lectures became the driving force
Dialogue: 10,0:02:59.95,0:03:03.43,Narrator,,0,0,0,,that gave a powerful boost to Kansai’s productivity.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:03.43,0:03:08.27,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Shinichi delivered his fiery lectures \Nin the third-floor hall of the Kansai Headquarters
Dialogue: 10,0:03:08.27,0:03:10.88,Narrator,,0,0,0,,right after the 8 a.m. service.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:10.88,0:03:14.17,Narrator,,0,0,0,,The guidance and content of Shinichi’s lectures
Dialogue: 10,0:03:14.17,0:03:17.24,Narrator,,0,0,0,,reached the hearts \Nof other members that very same day,
Dialogue: 10,0:03:17.24,0:03:22.09,Narrator,,0,0,0,,stirring everyone in the Kansai Branch \Nto give their all in the fight,
Dialogue: 10,0:03:22.09,0:03:26.59,Narrator,,0,0,0,,moved by Shinichi’s unwavering commitment to making the impossible possible.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:26.59,0:03:29.17,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 10,0:03:29.17,0:03:33.67,Thought,,0,0,0,,When should I put into practice \Nwhat Sensei instructed me to do the other day?
Dialogue: 10,0:03:33.67,0:03:38.80,Thought,,0,0,0,,It might just become the key to this battle. \NThat's what Sensei said...
Dialogue: 10,0:03:41.05,0:03:42.12,Top,,0,0,0,,Shinichi,
Dialogue: 10,0:03:42.12,0:03:45.48,Top,,0,0,0,,you really managed to get Kansai fired up.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:45.48,0:03:46.38,Top,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:46.38,0:03:50.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Kansai is a city of merchants, \Nso once you indicate the few critical points,
Dialogue: 10,0:03:50.48,0:03:53.88,Default,,0,0,0,,you can just step back \Nand marvel at their inventiveness.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:54.54,0:03:59.72,Default,,0,0,0,,From now on, the key question will be: \N"How to make the best use of it?"
Dialogue: 10,0:03:59.72,0:04:02.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. I was pondering that too.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:02.68,0:04:07.03,Default,,0,0,0,,In Kansai, we dedicated January through March \Nto offering individual guidance,
Dialogue: 10,0:04:07.03,0:04:11.19,Default,,0,0,0,,and now the entire organization \Nis alive with devotion.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:11.19,0:04:14.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Moreover, your bimonthly advanced lectures \Nand scripture lectures
Dialogue: 10,0:04:14.65,0:04:18.67,Default,,0,0,0,,instilled our values in people, \Ngiving rise to new Soka Gakkai champions
Dialogue: 10,0:04:18.67,0:04:20.82,Default,,0,0,0,,who breathe fresh life into our activities.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:20.82,0:04:25.42,Default,,0,0,0,,I felt that work in squads \Nwas no longer optimal for us. {han = 班 = smaller unit, like 5-8 ppl}
Dialogue: 10,0:04:25.42,0:04:28.60,Default,,0,0,0,,So starting in April, we shifted to working in bigger groups,
Dialogue: 10,0:04:28.60,0:04:31.89,Default,,0,0,0,,entrusting immediate on-site decisions to each group leader. {lit: let the boss fight in a spontaneous/voluntary way - think he means this, generally about giving the unit leader more tactical freedom in the field; kumi = 組 = unit bigger than han, like 15-30 ppl}
Dialogue: 10,0:04:31.89,0:04:33.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, fine by me.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:33.94,0:04:37.91,Default,,0,0,0,,If we build up the group leaders’ confidence, \Nit’ll only add fuel to the fire.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:37.91,0:04:43.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, I believe the realization that "We can save people too" will send out powerful ripples.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:43.99,0:04:50.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, that’s absolutely right. Shinichi, \Ndon’t let anyone stand in the way of your vision.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:50.33,0:04:51.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Do me this favor.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:51.81,0:04:57.59,Thought,,0,0,0,,All right, I’ll announce the launch of group-based fighting at the group leader meeting on April 1st.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:57.59,0:05:00.69,Thought,,0,0,0,,Using the general meeting on the 8th as a springboard,
Dialogue: 10,0:05:00.69,0:05:03.87,Thought,,0,0,0,,we’ll unleash a tsunami \Nof propagation in April and May! {take a giant leap forward and }
Dialogue: 10,0:05:04.87,0:05:08.35,Narrator,,0,0,0,,The results of March proselytizing \Nhave been published.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:08.35,0:05:12.48,Narrator,,0,0,0,,The Osaka branch achieved \Nan unprecedented success of 5,500 households,
Dialogue: 10,0:05:12.48,0:05:14.73,Narrator,,0,0,0,,ranking first nationwide.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:14.73,0:05:17.19,Narrator,,0,0,0,,The Sakai branch also did reasonably well,
Dialogue: 10,0:05:17.19,0:05:21.05,Narrator,,0,0,0,,converting 759 households, \Nand coming in 9th out of 16 branches.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:21.05,0:05:25.51,Narrator,,0,0,0,,The spirit of Kansai, poised to reach the heavens, \Nwas finally beginning to show.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:26.16,0:05:29.98,NarrTop,,0,0,0,,Group leaders and their detail \Nfrom across the Kansai region
Dialogue: 10,0:05:29.98,0:05:33.33,NarrTop,,0,0,0,,came together for an electrifying training session. {/and their staff}
Dialogue: 10,0:05:33.78,0:05:38.29,Default,,0,0,0,,With everyone's approval, we're finally switching to group-based work starting today.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:38.96,0:05:43.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Use your wisdom and creativity to host more and more of enjoyable roundtable discussions.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:44.39,0:05:50.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Let us make the next Joint Branch Meeting a great success with our own hands!
Dialogue: 10,0:05:50.29,0:05:51.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you with me?
Dialogue: 10,0:05:51.56,0:05:52.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes!
Dialogue: 10,0:06:03.61,0:06:07.34,Thought,,0,0,0,,I don't like it that there's just one entrance.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:07.34,0:06:11.29,Thought,,0,0,0,,If that many people gather there at once, \Nit could turn into a mess.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:11.29,0:06:14.80,Thought,,0,0,0,,We need to make sure \Nthe joint meeting goes off without a hitch.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:14.80,0:06:15.86,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 10,0:06:16.41,0:06:17.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Hello!
Dialogue: 10,0:06:17.36,0:06:19.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Oya-kun, hello!
Dialogue: 10,0:06:19.35,0:06:23.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey boss, the weather is wonderful outside \Nand sakura is in full bloom.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:24.76,0:06:27.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Why don't we go for a little walk?
Dialogue: 10,0:06:28.16,0:06:30.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's see...\NIt's 2 o'clock.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:30.78,0:06:33.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Oya-kun, how long does it take to get to Nara?
Dialogue: 10,0:06:33.69,0:06:37.31,Default,,0,0,0,,About an hour by express train, I think?
Dialogue: 10,0:06:37.31,0:06:39.05,Default,,0,0,0,,I see...\NOkay, let's go!
Dialogue: 10,0:06:51.51,0:06:54.91,Default,,0,0,0,,A refreshing atmosphere and bracing breeze...
Dialogue: 10,0:06:54.91,0:06:57.50,Default,,0,0,0,,It's just the oasis of serenity that I needed. {lit: "there are brief moments of leisure even when at one's busiest," this is exactly it}
Dialogue: 10,0:06:58.29,0:07:00.41,Default,,0,0,0,,That hits the spot!
Dialogue: 10,0:07:03.52,0:07:06.51,Thought,,0,0,0,,I want to be like that cloud—
Dialogue: 10,0:07:06.51,0:07:10.41,Thought,,0,0,0,,a man who drifts through life with ease, \Nno matter what comes his way.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:11.95,0:07:16.46,Thought,,0,0,0,,But even that craft can only \Nbe acquired through fighting.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:20.48,0:07:22.66,Default,,0,0,0,,All right. \NLet's double back, Oya-kun.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:22.66,0:07:25.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh? Already, sir?\NI thought we just came!
Dialogue: 10,0:07:25.71,0:07:31.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I already feel fully recharged—now it’s time we spread that sense of lightness to everyone else. {to enliven one's spirit; to refresh oneself; to cheer oneself up}
Dialogue: 10,0:07:31.69,0:07:32.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Right...
Dialogue: 10,0:07:33.41,0:07:34.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's go now!
Dialogue: 10,0:07:38.35,0:07:41.49,NarrTop,,0,0,0,,April 8th, 1958.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:41.49,0:07:45.32,NarrTop,,0,0,0,,In Osaka, the rain began last night \Nand hasn’t let up since.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:46.90,0:07:49.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Even sprinkling sand \Non the walkways won't do now! {woven mat (esp. one made of straw)​ -- no idea what he refers to; “むしろ”に砂をまいたぐらいではとてもあきまへん; actually could be "surrounding territory outside of stadium"}
Dialogue: 10,0:07:50.43,0:07:53.14,Default,,0,0,0,,It's so muddy you can't walk on it!
Dialogue: 10,0:07:53.14,0:07:56.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you saying we just say, \N"Nah, too wet," to the path Sensei chose?
Dialogue: 10,0:07:56.62,0:08:00.81,Default,,0,0,0,,In that case, why don’t we lay down \Nsome tents on the walkways? {hope he means "to walk on" and not how you'd usually set up a tent}
Dialogue: 10,0:08:00.81,0:08:02.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Better that than the mud. {lit: I don't think it'll sink - probably means "in mud", could refer to the tent itself or to the visitors}
Dialogue: 10,0:08:02.77,0:08:07.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Good thinking! All right, let's split and find some tents to borrow!
Dialogue: 10,0:08:07.07,0:08:10.51,Default,,0,0,0,,We're really stripped for time, though. \NDo you understand the task?
Dialogue: 10,0:08:10.51,0:08:11.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Understood!
Dialogue: 10,0:08:11.33,0:08:12.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, let's go!
Dialogue: 10,0:08:18.46,0:08:21.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Those who are headed \Nto Osaka Stadium, this way!
Dialogue: 10,0:08:21.33,0:08:24.98,Default,,0,0,0,,It's raining, so please watch your step!
Dialogue: 10,0:08:26.29,0:08:27.78,Default,,0,0,0,,What's up with these guys?
Dialogue: 10,0:08:28.47,0:08:31.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey mister, is there anything to see at Osaka Stadium?
Dialogue: 10,0:08:31.72,0:08:33.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Soka Gakkai general meeting!
Dialogue: 10,0:08:33.93,0:08:35.17,Default,,0,0,0,,In this rain?
Dialogue: 10,0:08:35.17,0:08:35.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes!
Dialogue: 10,0:08:35.85,0:08:37.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Whew...
Dialogue: 10,0:08:39.46,0:08:43.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Yamamoto-kun, it's raining really hard. \NWhy don't we cancel it?
Dialogue: 10,0:08:44.07,0:08:49.57,Default,,0,0,0,,I considered that too. But our Kansai comrades are full of enthusiasm.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:49.57,0:08:53.26,Default,,0,0,0,,That's true. \NIf we cancel it now, it'll be a big stink.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:53.78,0:08:54.93,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you mean?
Dialogue: 10,0:08:55.48,0:08:58.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Early this morning, \Nthe group and squad leaders
Dialogue: 10,0:08:58.43,0:09:02.46,Default,,0,0,0,,came to me, eyes blazing—\N“Branch chief, we’re doing this, right?”
Dialogue: 10,0:09:02.46,0:09:06.38,Default,,0,0,0,,If we cancel now, we’ll kill the great momentum we’ve built up so far.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:06.38,0:09:07.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Please proceed with the meeting!
Dialogue: 10,0:09:10.23,0:09:12.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd also like to ask you to forge ahead.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:12.72,0:09:17.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Our comrades from remote areas such as Shikoku and Okayama already hit the road.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:17.11,0:09:18.58,Default,,0,0,0,,And they can't turn back!
Dialogue: 10,0:09:19.10,0:09:21.02,Default,,0,0,0,,That's what troubles me.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:21.02,0:09:24.66,Default,,0,0,0,,If we order a cancellation now, \Nchaos will break out.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:24.66,0:09:27.55,Default,,0,0,0,,In any case, let's take a look at the site first.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:27.55,0:09:29.61,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 10,0:09:35.58,0:09:37.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Sensei,
Dialogue: 10,0:09:37.24,0:09:39.60,Default,,0,0,0,,it's pouring rain. \NI'm sorry...
Dialogue: 10,0:09:40.00,0:09:44.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe it’s the heavens telling us \Nthat the battle ahead won't be easy.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:44.81,0:09:45.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes...
Dialogue: 10,0:09:45.67,0:09:46.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you have a plan?
Dialogue: 10,0:09:46.61,0:09:52.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. I’ll head to the site right away to assess the situation and decide whether or not we cancel it.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:52.03,0:09:53.32,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 10,0:09:53.32,0:09:55.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Please wait until then.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:55.95,0:09:57.24,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:58.25,0:10:01.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Please proceed slowly in two lines!
Dialogue: 10,0:10:09.36,0:10:12.68,Thought,,0,0,0,,No one seems the least bit bothered by the rain.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:13.20,0:10:15.26,Thought,,0,0,0,,It's like there's no downpour at all. {lit: completely to make light of; to hold lightly}
Dialogue: 10,0:10:18.20,0:10:19.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Good morning!
Dialogue: 10,0:10:19.16,0:10:20.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, Boss!
Dialogue: 10,0:10:20.39,0:10:21.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Good morning!
Dialogue: 10,0:10:22.41,0:10:26.61,Default,,0,0,0,,To you too, Asada-kun. You got the latest estimates on the amount of participants on site? {/who showed up by now}
Dialogue: 10,0:10:26.61,0:10:31.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, we've just broke through the 3,500 mark.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:31.02,0:10:33.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I see. The entryway is in order? {lit: entrance is going as planned?}
Dialogue: 10,0:10:33.76,0:10:36.38,Default,,0,0,0,,No, we opened the gates a bit earlier—at 9.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:36.38,0:10:41.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Good call. If you hadn’t opened it early, \Nthe walkways would’ve gotten jammed.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:41.98,0:10:42.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes!
Dialogue: 10,0:10:42.62,0:10:45.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Mitsui-san, any updates on other prefectures? {lit: what's the status of departures in each prefecture}
Dialogue: 10,0:10:45.73,0:10:46.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:46.21,0:10:52.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Charter buses from Kyoto and Wakayama \Nare already on their way here.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:52.32,0:10:56.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Buses from Okayama, Kurashiki, Kanazawa and Fukui left in the evening. {/set out last night}
Dialogue: 10,0:10:57.24,0:11:01.95,Default,,0,0,0,,The ship from Kochi has already docked in Osaka, \Nso people should be arriving any minute now.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:01.95,0:11:03.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay. Got it.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:03.35,0:11:05.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Chief, we're rolling with it, aren't we?
Dialogue: 10,0:11:05.60,0:11:07.81,Default,,0,0,0,,No, we don't know for sure yet...
Dialogue: 10,0:11:07.81,0:11:11.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Everyone is already on their way here.\NOf course we should do it!
Dialogue: 10,0:11:11.25,0:11:15.10,Default,,0,0,0,,I’d like to, but I’d rather wait and see \Nhow things play out before deciding.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:15.84,0:11:19.45,Default,,0,0,0,,First, I’ll walk around the venue \Nand encourage our staff.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:22.81,0:11:24.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Keep up the good work!
Dialogue: 10,0:11:26.14,0:11:27.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Towels for the people? {lit: what is that cloth for - needs to be phrased this way to justify "yes" in the next line}
Dialogue: 10,0:11:27.46,0:11:34.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. We’ll hand them out to everyone arriving, \Nso they can at least have a dry seat.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:34.21,0:11:37.03,Default,,0,0,0,,I see, so it's for wiping the seats?
Dialogue: 10,0:11:37.03,0:11:39.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you. \NDid you borrow these somewhere?
Dialogue: 10,0:11:39.78,0:11:43.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. A member living in the neighborhood lent it to us.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:43.95,0:11:46.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Give them my thanks too later!
Dialogue: 10,0:11:46.63,0:11:47.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay!
Dialogue: 10,0:11:48.50,0:11:55.78,Default,,0,0,0,,{generic "yes, here you go"}
Dialogue: 10,0:11:59.53,0:12:02.08,Thought,,0,0,0,,Even the bleachers are starting to fill up.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:02.08,0:12:05.37,Thought,,0,0,0,,Our Kansai comrades \Nare unfazed by wind and rain.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:05.37,0:12:09.94,Thought,,0,0,0,,They’re probably full of confidence, \Nknowing they successfully fought their way here. {means "to get to this point"}
Dialogue: 10,0:12:09.94,0:12:15.38,Thought,,0,0,0,,Nothing can stop the momentum we built during the establishment phase any longer.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:15.38,0:12:20.60,Thought,,0,0,0,,If we win even under these worst-case conditions, an unshakable conviction in Soka Gakkai
Dialogue: 10,0:12:20.60,0:12:22.89,Thought,,0,0,0,,will take root in the hearts of our Kansai members.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:22.89,0:12:26.85,Thought,,0,0,0,,All right, let's go ahead. \NWe're doing it!
Dialogue: 10,0:12:33.17,0:12:35.75,Narrator,,0,0,0,,And so, by the order
Dialogue: 10,0:12:35.75,0:12:38.93,Narrator,,0,0,0,,of Kansai Commander-in-Chief Yamamoto Shinichi,
Dialogue: 10,0:12:38.93,0:12:44.49,Narrator,,0,0,0,,the Joint Osaka–Sakai Branch Meeting began at 1 p.m. amid pouring rain.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:03.93,0:13:07.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Our president, Toda-sensei, often says,
Dialogue: 10,0:13:07.75,0:13:10.87,Default,,0,0,0,,“We must return, in spirit, \Nto the time of Nichiren Daishonin—
Dialogue: 10,0:13:10.87,0:13:14.11,Default,,0,0,0,,that was the last era in Japan when
Dialogue: 10,0:13:14.11,0:13:18.73,Default,,0,0,0,,the true Buddhist spirit of individual enlightenment was alive.”
Dialogue: 10,0:13:18.73,0:13:23.35,Default,,0,0,0,,With the conviction that our work for the Common Path today
Dialogue: 10,0:13:23.35,0:13:28.33,Default,,0,0,0,,is grounded in the faith that connects us to Nichiren Daishonin’s time,
Dialogue: 10,0:13:28.33,0:13:32.17,Default,,0,0,0,,why don’t we use today’s general meeting as a springboard for the next step
Dialogue: 10,0:13:32.17,0:13:34.54,Default,,0,0,0,,in our fight to save the people?
Dialogue: 10,0:13:34.54,0:13:37.38,Default,,0,0,0,,{Yeah!}
Dialogue: 10,0:13:45.62,0:13:46.74,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 10,0:13:46.74,0:13:48.42,Default,,0,0,0,,The rain let up!
Dialogue: 10,0:13:48.42,0:13:49.89,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 10,0:13:50.41,0:13:52.95,Default,,0,0,0,,It really did! \NThe rain let up!
Dialogue: 10,0:13:52.95,0:13:53.89,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 10,0:14:06.14,0:14:10.12,Default,,0,0,0,,I am a disciple of Nichiren Daishonin.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:10.12,0:14:12.74,Default,,0,0,0,,And I believe that a disciple of Daishonin
Dialogue: 10,0:14:12.74,0:14:18.05,Default,,0,0,0,,must have in him the unwavering resolve \Nthat the Common Path can be achieved.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:18.63,0:14:19.84,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 10,0:14:20.33,0:14:21.55,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 10,0:14:21.55,0:14:25.02,Default,,0,0,0,,You may then ask: \N"When will the Common Path be achieved?"
Dialogue: 10,0:14:25.02,0:14:27.07,Default,,0,0,0,,And the answer is now!
Dialogue: 10,0:14:27.07,0:14:28.73,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the present! {/our times}
Dialogue: 10,0:14:28.73,0:14:32.66,Default,,0,0,0,,When we advance Buddhism through every part of society,
Dialogue: 10,0:14:32.66,0:14:35.85,Default,,0,0,0,,allowing people to see things clearly and correctly through it;
Dialogue: 10,0:14:35.85,0:14:42.03,Default,,0,0,0,,when our contribution to the happiness and peace of all becomes evident to the naked eye,
Dialogue: 10,0:14:42.55,0:14:46.49,Default,,0,0,0,,that’s when we know \Nthe Common Path has been achieved!
Dialogue: 10,0:14:55.23,0:14:57.46,Default,,0,0,0,,We’ve got the final tally of attendees!
Dialogue: 10,0:14:57.96,0:14:58.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Here!
Dialogue: 10,0:14:59.44,0:15:02.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Oya-kun! Over 20,000 visitors are attending!
Dialogue: 10,0:15:02.42,0:15:03.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh? For real?!
Dialogue: 10,0:15:03.51,0:15:05.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah! Isn't it amazing?
Dialogue: 10,0:15:05.06,0:15:06.66,Default,,0,0,0,,We really did it!
Dialogue: 10,0:15:06.66,0:15:08.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Everyone thought it was next to impossible,
Dialogue: 10,0:15:08.91,0:15:13.90,Default,,0,0,0,,but thanks to Chief Yamamoto’s guidance, \Nwe really tore through those numbers! {/properly reached that amount}
Dialogue: 10,0:15:13.90,0:15:16.27,Default,,0,0,0,,What great insight he has! {lit: what was he reading - idk maybe he literally means "what books did yamamoto read to do this"; 一体どうゆう読みをしてたんやろ?}
Dialogue: 10,0:15:16.27,0:15:18.21,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't get better than that! {lit: don't know that; also no clue what he means; そんなもん分からへんわい}
Dialogue: 10,0:15:18.21,0:15:21.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, if we can match our gear \Nwith the chief, we'll win! {idk what he means anymore}
Dialogue: 10,0:15:22.46,0:15:26.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Soka Gakkai exists to spread the Common Path.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:26.37,0:15:29.45,Default,,0,0,0,,You all understand keenly this fundamental truth.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:29.45,0:15:35.43,Default,,0,0,0,,For your own sake and for society, \Nmove forward with full confidence in all you do.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:36.39,0:15:40.30,Default,,0,0,0,,This concludes my today's address.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:42.25,0:15:46.59,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Inspired by the success of the joint general meeting, Kansai erupted with energy.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:46.59,0:15:49.85,Narrator,,0,0,0,,A wave of confidence \Nand joy swept through Kansai,
Dialogue: 10,0:15:49.85,0:15:53.85,Narrator,,0,0,0,,with group meetings and roundtable discussions \Nspringing up day and night,
Dialogue: 10,0:15:53.85,0:15:56.94,Narrator,,0,0,0,,reigniting the flame of propagation \Nall over the place.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:57.44,0:15:58.90,Thought,,0,0,0,,What's going on?!
Dialogue: 10,0:15:59.40,0:16:04.41,Thought,,0,0,0,,Ever since that general meeting, Chief’s been {spontaneously }setting up roundtable discussions nonstop—
Dialogue: 10,0:16:04.41,0:16:06.59,Thought,,0,0,0,,I haven’t had a minute to rest!
Dialogue: 10,0:16:06.59,0:16:08.97,Thought,,0,0,0,,And it's been like that for days on end!
Dialogue: 10,0:16:10.43,0:16:13.97,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you say? Won't it be your loss if you miss your chance for happiness? {literal - refrain of "kansai people never miss a profit"}
Dialogue: 10,0:16:13.97,0:16:18.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Incense and candles are all you need.\NWhat do you say, my good sir?
Dialogue: 10,0:16:18.12,0:16:19.42,Default,,0,0,0,,I suppose we could try...
Dialogue: 10,0:16:19.42,0:16:20.86,Default,,0,0,0,,What about you, my friend?
Dialogue: 10,0:16:20.86,0:16:22.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, we'll do it.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:22.59,0:16:26.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Congratulations!\NLet's do our best together!
Dialogue: 10,0:16:26.58,0:16:29.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, thanks a bunch.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:29.51,0:16:35.02,Default,,0,0,0,,But I still can't quite believe it—\Nall my friends who tagged along wished to join!
Dialogue: 10,0:16:35.02,0:16:38.04,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s the power of everyone \Nin the organization—Chief included—
Dialogue: 10,0:16:38.04,0:16:40.81,Default,,0,0,0,,sincerely wishing for our comrades' happiness.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:40.81,0:16:45.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Now all they need is to receive their altar decorations and remember to pray. {gohonzon}
Dialogue: 10,0:16:45.50,0:16:46.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Sure!
Dialogue: 10,0:16:46.75,0:16:48.65,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Early morning scripture lectures,
Dialogue: 10,0:16:48.65,0:16:54.00,Narrator,,0,0,0,,the rainy general meeting, \Nand the push for group-level activities
Dialogue: 10,0:16:54.00,0:16:56.07,Narrator,,0,0,0,,gave the Kansai Branch new momentum,
Dialogue: 10,0:16:56.07,0:17:01.69,Narrator,,0,0,0,,driving a major leap forward \Nin the ongoing fight for propagation.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:01.69,0:17:07.30,Narrator,,0,0,0,,But in the midst of it all, the evil that breaks the unity of comrades was secretly creeping in,
Dialogue: 10,0:17:07.30,0:17:10.93,Narrator,,0,0,0,,and no one was there to notice it approaching.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:12.89,0:17:13.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Mitsui-san,
Dialogue: 10,0:17:13.93,0:17:17.25,Default,,0,0,0,,let's give the squad chief another scolding.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:17.25,0:17:19.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Tell him his numbers are insufficient. {/say "produce better results"}
Dialogue: 10,0:17:19.10,0:17:24.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Sir... I’ve already encouraged \Nhim and told him to give it his all more than once.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:24.25,0:17:26.07,Default,,0,0,0,,I don’t think I should push him any more.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:26.07,0:17:30.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Mitsui-san, once you take the lead in battle, \Nyou’ve got to launch a full-on attack.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:30.97,0:17:34.08,Default,,0,0,0,,If we miss this chance, \Nwe won't be able to do any fighting.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:34.08,0:17:35.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, but still...
Dialogue: 10,0:17:36.43,0:17:41.52,Thought,,0,0,0,,This guy thinks he knows best \Njust 'cause they sent him from Tokyo...
Dialogue: 10,0:17:41.52,0:17:44.79,Thought,,0,0,0,,But only an Osakan truly knows \Nwhat’s best for him! {lit: for naniwa, there's a naniwa way of doing things; Naniwa = former name for Osaka region and typical proper name in kansai}
Dialogue: 10,0:17:46.07,0:17:48.08,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you say, friends?
Dialogue: 10,0:17:48.90,0:17:51.88,Default,,0,0,0,,He'd never realize it if we keep silent!
Dialogue: 10,0:17:51.88,0:17:54.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Tsuchida-san, what do you think?\NDon't you agree?
Dialogue: 10,0:17:55.49,0:18:00.93,Default,,0,0,0,,I think... Group Leader is still learning the ropes, \Nso we shouldn't flog him too much. {lit: just recently started to work on his own so it's better not to stir/instigate too much - kumicho / group leader is not the same as hancho / squad chief previously so idk what he means, either they mixed it up or kumicho is the gray-haired guy right here and hancho is someone else}
Dialogue: 10,0:18:02.12,0:18:03.42,Default,,0,0,0,,What did you say?!
Dialogue: 10,0:18:03.42,0:18:04.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Tomii-san,
Dialogue: 10,0:18:04.86,0:18:07.96,Default,,0,0,0,,we Osakans don't like being pressured.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:07.96,0:18:11.15,Default,,0,0,0,,The overall numbers are coming along, \Nso let's not push our luck. {lit: we're producing the results so just watch it}
Dialogue: 10,0:18:11.15,0:18:13.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Just as the perfect chance presented itself...
Dialogue: 10,0:18:14.52,0:18:17.54,Thought,,0,0,0,,Can't believe those Osakans \Nwillingly chose to be clueless!
Dialogue: 10,0:18:17.54,0:18:20.95,Thought,,0,0,0,,I try to teach them to fight, \Nbut they won't even listen!
Dialogue: 10,0:18:26.52,0:18:31.82,Thought,,0,0,0,,The clash between them seems to come from differences in how they carry out their activities.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:31.82,0:18:36.45,Thought,,0,0,0,,At this point, it’s best to let each one share his view and work things out through discussion.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:36.45,0:18:38.68,Thought,,0,0,0,,We don't need any tension in our ranks. {lingering discomfort; uneasiness; bad aftertaste; unpleasant feeling​}
Dialogue: 10,0:18:38.68,0:18:43.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Being proactive and being complacent \Naren't the same thing! {lit: spontaneous activity and letting someone do as they please are different in nature}
Dialogue: 10,0:18:43.06,0:18:45.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't you understand the dangers
Dialogue: 10,0:18:45.38,0:18:49.46,Default,,0,0,0,,of letting one run wild wherever they want \Nif you don't hold the reins tightly?!
Dialogue: 10,0:18:49.46,0:18:52.76,Default,,0,0,0,,That's what reporting in advance is for. {そらぁ 事前に報告は取りますわ}
Dialogue: 10,0:18:52.76,0:18:54.89,Default,,0,0,0,,But don’t you get that sometimes
Dialogue: 10,0:18:54.89,0:18:58.14,Default,,0,0,0,,we need to hold a roundtable on short notice for newcomers? {literal, idk what he means}
Dialogue: 10,0:18:58.14,0:18:59.58,Default,,0,0,0,,So what of it?
Dialogue: 10,0:18:59.58,0:19:05.96,Default,,0,0,0,,How's that not obvious? We need to make \Nthe reporting system more lenient!
Dialogue: 10,0:19:05.96,0:19:09.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyone would get fed up\Nif you're watching his every move!
Dialogue: 10,0:19:10.00,0:19:15.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Friends! This isn’t a productive discussion—\Nit’s just an emotional back-and-forth!
Dialogue: 10,0:19:15.27,0:19:18.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Tomii-kun, who do you think the enemy is?
Dialogue: 10,0:19:19.02,0:19:21.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Are our local leaders friends or foes?
Dialogue: 10,0:19:23.08,0:19:24.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Friends, sir...
Dialogue: 10,0:19:27.55,0:19:31.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Then why should we have \Nto fight and quarrel with our friends?
Dialogue: 10,0:19:39.26,0:19:43.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Sharing opinions is healthy, \Nbut clashing emotions is just a petty squabble!
Dialogue: 10,0:19:43.58,0:19:46.33,Default,,0,0,0,,If anything, it undermines \Nthe fighting power of your allies!
Dialogue: 10,0:19:48.04,0:19:51.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Tomii-kun, that was really unsightly of you.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:51.86,0:19:54.55,Default,,0,0,0,,When did you embrace this poison of pride? {lit: when did you become so zoujoman = someone who hasn't attained enlightenment but acts conceited as if he already did}
Dialogue: 10,0:19:54.55,0:19:57.95,Default,,0,0,0,,You see the slightest sign of progress \Nand already let it go to your head?
Dialogue: 10,0:19:57.95,0:20:01.45,Default,,0,0,0,,You've let the demon of vanity \Nand lust for recognition take over. {omitting "Me, me, me!"}{/demon/evil}
Dialogue: 10,0:20:01.45,0:20:03.85,Default,,0,0,0,,You’ve let the worst in you show itself.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:03.85,0:20:08.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you understand my chagrin for pledging my full trust to you?
Dialogue: 10,0:20:09.33,0:20:12.77,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry.\NI'm really guilty before you!
Dialogue: 10,0:20:13.59,0:20:16.74,Default,,0,0,0,,I was foolish. \NPlease accept my apology!
Dialogue: 10,0:20:16.74,0:20:20.70,Default,,0,0,0,,I will never let this transpire again!
Dialogue: 10,0:20:21.10,0:20:27.71,Thought,,0,0,0,,Chief is right—it wasn’t an exchange of opinions, just me losing my cool.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:27.71,0:20:30.17,Thought,,0,0,0,,Tomii-san got carried away giving orders, {one after another}
Dialogue: 10,0:20:30.17,0:20:33.71,Thought,,0,0,0,,so I snapped, "Don’t you know how tough it is for those of us on the ground?!"
Dialogue: 10,0:20:33.71,0:20:37.22,Thought,,0,0,0,,To me, that seemed like he was being arrogant...
Dialogue: 10,0:20:37.94,0:20:40.64,Thought,,0,0,0,,It's me who needs to be reprimanded!
Dialogue: 10,0:20:46.56,0:20:51.48,Default,,0,0,0,,You just saw me giving quite a scolding to our comrade I brought from Tokyo.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:51.48,0:20:53.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you know why I did that?
Dialogue: 10,0:20:56.27,0:20:59.84,Default,,0,0,0,,There are demons standing in our way to victory, \Nand they’re who I’m fighting!
Dialogue: 10,0:21:01.52,0:21:06.95,Default,,0,0,0,,You guys get so proud of yourselves \Njust because we had a decent start to our plan.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:06.95,0:21:08.68,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s unbelievable!
Dialogue: 10,0:21:08.68,0:21:12.04,Default,,0,0,0,,No one noticed that you let \Nthe Demon of Pride pull you around!
Dialogue: 10,0:21:13.50,0:21:17.24,Default,,0,0,0,,It made you get emotional over small things, \Nforgetting our enemy
Dialogue: 10,0:21:17.24,0:21:20.27,Default,,0,0,0,,and turning on each other with criticism and ripostes!
Dialogue: 10,0:21:20.27,0:21:22.78,Default,,0,0,0,,How did you allow this to happen?
Dialogue: 10,0:21:22.78,0:21:26.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Aren't we all here the only friends we have? {lit: allied leaders - aren't we here the only ones there are?}
Dialogue: 10,0:21:26.56,0:21:29.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Where else do we have any friends?
Dialogue: 10,0:21:29.64,0:21:34.73,Default,,0,0,0,,All the criticism and slander aimed at tearing apart our unity is the demons' scheme!
Dialogue: 10,0:21:35.19,0:21:39.69,Thought,,0,0,0,,I see... So it was the demons' doing?\NI gotta be more careful.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:39.69,0:21:45.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Without the unity of dispatched and local leaders, we have no chance of winning this battle!
Dialogue: 10,0:21:45.61,0:21:48.81,Default,,0,0,0,,What matters is how we achieve this unity.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:48.81,0:21:50.94,Default,,0,0,0,,The scripture on the unity of minds says,
Dialogue: 10,0:21:50.94,0:21:53.84,Default,,0,0,0,,"When your minds are united, \Nyou can achieve anything,
Dialogue: 10,0:21:53.84,0:21:57.65,Default,,0,0,0,,but if you’re divided, \Nnothing will come to fruition." {lit: if different bodies one mind, anything is possible, if one body different minds, nothing will come true}
Dialogue: 10,0:21:57.65,0:22:03.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Daishonin told us, "The key to victory in battle lies in whether or not we are united in spirit."
Dialogue: 10,0:22:04.13,0:22:08.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Nothing is more important \Nfor us right now than that unity of spirit!
Dialogue: 10,0:22:08.56,0:22:13.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Only defeat awaits those who enter that battle \Nwith a divided spirit!
Dialogue: 10,0:22:14.73,0:22:18.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Whether we win or lose, \Nit all comes down to our shared goal. {/determination}
Dialogue: 10,0:22:19.03,0:22:23.64,Default,,0,0,0,,We need to realize that even the slightest friction between dispatched and local leaders
Dialogue: 10,0:22:23.64,0:22:26.32,Default,,0,0,0,,can completely shatter our unity!
Dialogue: 10,0:22:26.32,0:22:28.22,Default,,0,0,0,,This issue can't be overlooked!
Dialogue: 10,0:22:29.04,0:22:32.33,Default,,0,0,0,,So? Tomii-kun, Mitsui-san, \Ndo you understand?
Dialogue: 10,0:22:32.77,0:22:34.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes! It's clear to me now.
Dialogue: 10,0:22:34.50,0:22:37.67,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm the only one \Nwho should be apologizing here.
Dialogue: 10,0:22:38.57,0:22:43.63,Default,,0,0,0,,I’m counting on you two to lead the 1st District \Nto glorious victory from here on out.
Dialogue: 10,0:22:43.63,0:22:46.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't let the petty conflicts tear you apart again. {lit: get along and in unity, do your best}
Dialogue: 10,0:22:46.39,0:22:49.57,Default,,0,0,0,,We won't! Thank you!
Dialogue: 10,0:22:52.02,0:22:54.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Forgive me for repeating myself,
Dialogue: 10,0:22:54.04,0:22:59.74,Default,,0,0,0,,but we won’t win this battle unless we make \Ndeepening our faith our top priority.
Dialogue: 10,0:22:59.74,0:23:01.07,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 10,0:23:01.07,0:23:05.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Some of you might feel the results are lacking \Nand progress is hard to see.
Dialogue: 10,0:23:06.58,0:23:12.75,Default,,0,0,0,,But no power in the world is more fearsome\Nthan steady progress grounded in faith.
Dialogue: 10,0:23:12.75,0:23:15.52,Default,,0,0,0,,How can we be sure of that?
Dialogue: 10,0:23:15.52,0:23:19.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, that's where your fight \Nas the leaders comes into play. {それを確信できるかどうか そこに諸君たちの責任者としての戦いがあるのだ}
Dialogue: 10,0:23:22.96,0:23:27.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Sawada-kun, I get that the Tokyo Branch is focusing on roundtable discussions—
Dialogue: 10,0:23:27.32,0:23:29.64,Default,,0,0,0,,but isn't it at the expense of propagation? {沢田君 東京は座談会を中心に動いているということだが活動が上滑りしている のではないか?}
Dialogue: 10,0:23:29.64,0:23:33.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Y-Yes... But everyone \Nis fighting with all they've got.
Dialogue: 10,0:23:33.60,0:23:36.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Why can't you produce good results, then?
Dialogue: 10,0:23:36.10,0:23:39.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe it's because there's no unity of faith?
Dialogue: 10,0:23:39.06,0:23:41.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Y-Yes...
Dialogue: 10,0:23:41.07,0:23:43.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Tokyo is the city of boatmen.
Dialogue: 10,0:23:43.86,0:23:48.66,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why you must be \Nan epitome of piety yourself. {だからこそ信心という原点に君自身が立つ以外にない - I have no idea what it has to do with boatmen}
Dialogue: 10,0:23:49.26,0:23:52.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Only then the unity will be born.
Dialogue: 10,0:23:52.12,0:23:54.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Y-Yes!
Dialogue: 10,0:23:55.31,0:23:57.54,Thought,,0,0,0,,The Tokyo developments are worrying...
Dialogue: 10,0:23:57.54,0:24:00.81,Thought,,0,0,0,,But I don't think I can offer any support to them right now.
Dialogue: 10,0:24:00.81,0:24:08.07,Thought,,0,0,0,,If we don’t give our all to the Battle for Kansai, \NSensei’s vision will stay just a pipe dream.
Dialogue: 10,0:24:08.07,0:24:12.15,Thought,,0,0,0,,I can only pray for Tokyo's \Ngreat struggle and great victory.
Dialogue: 10,0:24:15.41,0:24:16.14,Top,,0,0,0,,Chief!
Dialogue: 10,0:24:16.77,0:24:19.94,Default,,0,0,0,,We’re just about to hit this month’s sales target.
Dialogue: 10,0:24:20.57,0:24:24.34,Default,,0,0,0,,What worries me is this final step. \NCan we really make it?
Dialogue: 10,0:24:24.34,0:24:25.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, I'm sure of it!
Dialogue: 10,0:24:25.92,0:24:27.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Good luck, then.
Dialogue: 10,0:24:29.11,0:24:31.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, Yamamoto here.
Dialogue: 10,0:24:31.60,0:24:33.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, it's you, Sei-chan?
Dialogue: 10,0:24:34.66,0:24:39.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Wait, what? 9,002 households for Osaka Branch, \N1,111 households for Sakai Branch?
Dialogue: 10,0:24:39.65,0:24:42.02,Default,,0,0,0,,You did it, Sei-chan!
Dialogue: 10,0:24:42.02,0:24:43.46,Default,,0,0,0,,{Yes, yes.}
Dialogue: 10,0:24:43.46,0:24:47.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Please give my heartfelt congratulations to the Asada Branch Chief.
Dialogue: 10,0:24:47.90,0:24:49.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll be in touch soon.
Dialogue: 10,0:24:50.78,0:24:54.22,Default,,0,0,0,,So Osaka made that last push \Nand racked up 9,002 households?
Dialogue: 10,0:24:54.22,0:24:54.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 10,0:24:54.91,0:24:58.06,Default,,0,0,0,,That's an unprecedented number \Nif I ever seen one!
Dialogue: 10,0:24:58.06,0:24:59.43,Default,,0,0,0,,So it seems.
Dialogue: 10,0:24:59.43,0:25:03.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Kamata Branch reported in yesterday \Nwith 3,401 households.
Dialogue: 10,0:25:03.62,0:25:05.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Which makes them #2 this month.
Dialogue: 10,0:25:05.32,0:25:10.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Lately, the Osaka Branch \Nhas held tight to that #1 spot.
Dialogue: 10,0:25:12.37,0:25:15.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, we can’t just sit back \Nand take it easy now, Sei-chan.
Dialogue: 10,0:25:15.33,0:25:20.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Finding a way to sustain that joy \Nwill be the key to winning in May.
Dialogue: 10,0:25:20.33,0:25:23.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, so after talking it over with everyone,
Dialogue: 10,0:25:23.82,0:25:27.30,Default,,0,0,0,,we decided to hold \Na branch execs' meeting on the 29th.
Dialogue: 10,0:25:27.30,0:25:29.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Branch execs' meeting?
Dialogue: 10,0:25:29.53,0:25:31.35,Default,,0,0,0,,{Yes, yes.}
Dialogue: 10,0:25:31.35,0:25:32.26,Default,,0,0,0,,For that...
Dialogue: 10,0:25:32.26,0:25:37.22,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll need to make three round trips \Nbetween Tokyo and Osaka in one week.
Dialogue: 10,0:25:37.74,0:25:40.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, got it.\NLet's go with 27th.
Dialogue: 10,0:25:41.36,0:25:44.75,Thought,,0,0,0,,Night train out, night train back... {/Going there at night and coming back at night...}
Dialogue: 10,0:25:44.75,0:25:48.41,Thought,,0,0,0,,But I can’t let the fire of motivation \Nburn out in Kansai.
Dialogue: 10,0:25:48.41,0:25:52.03,Thought,,0,0,0,,It's not the time to worry about my health. {僕も体がどうのなんて言っておられるものか!}
Dialogue: 10,0:25:59.00,0:26:03.96,NarrTop,,0,0,0,,On April 29th, \Nthe Osaka Branch Execs' Meeting was held
Dialogue: 10,0:26:03.96,0:26:06.73,NarrTop,,0,0,0,,at the Community Hall \Nin Kita Ward of Osaka City.
Dialogue: 10,0:26:06.73,0:26:11.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Our district set a goal \Nof 800 household converted in May.
Dialogue: 10,0:26:11.21,0:26:14.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Everyone in our district \Nwill work as one to achieve that goal!
Dialogue: 10,0:26:15.28,0:26:17.64,Default,,0,0,0,,We’re set on making it the top in our branch!
Dialogue: 10,0:26:17.64,0:26:22.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Everyone, please watch \Nour district's selfless fighting in May.
Dialogue: 10,0:26:22.06,0:26:24.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Our goal is 500 household conversions,
Dialogue: 10,0:26:24.18,0:26:29.36,Default,,0,0,0,,but easing even one more person’s suffering \Nwould mean just as much to us all!
Dialogue: 10,0:26:29.76,0:26:31.59,Thought,,0,0,0,,Their drive is incredible.
Dialogue: 10,0:26:31.59,0:26:38.03,Thought,,0,0,0,,I want to keep this irresistible momentum rolling \Nnot just through May, but all the way to July. {(with) great vigour (from the way splitting bamboo goes all down the stick); irresistible force​}
Dialogue: 10,0:26:42.64,0:26:45.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Life is like a theater drama.
Dialogue: 10,0:26:45.25,0:26:48.65,Default,,0,0,0,,When we live by the mission \Nof spreading the Common Path,
Dialogue: 10,0:26:48.65,0:26:53.93,Default,,0,0,0,,striving for both others' and our own happiness, \Nwe’re also playing out the drama of life.
Dialogue: 10,0:26:55.95,0:26:59.87,Default,,0,0,0,,I’m sure you all know the famous Napoleon, \Nwho played the role of a great hero
Dialogue: 10,0:26:59.87,0:27:02.43,Default,,0,0,0,,in 18th-century Europe.
Dialogue: 10,0:27:02.81,0:27:08.90,Default,,0,0,0,,When he invaded Russia, he commanded, "Advance!" and marched straight for Moscow.
Dialogue: 10,0:27:08.90,0:27:12.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, when he escaped from the Isle of Elba,
Dialogue: 10,0:27:12.34,0:27:16.41,Default,,0,0,0,,he commanded, "Advance!" \Nand marched on Paris.
Dialogue: 10,0:27:16.41,0:27:19.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Napoleon wasn't familiar with the Lotus Sutra.
Dialogue: 10,0:27:19.24,0:27:22.68,Default,,0,0,0,,I’m convinced that we, who’ve embraced \Nthat highest philosophy of life,
Dialogue: 10,0:27:22.68,0:27:26.75,Default,,0,0,0,,and taken up the cause of the Common Path, \Na global peace movement,
Dialogue: 10,0:27:26.75,0:27:31.02,Default,,0,0,0,,are a hundred million times greater than Napoleon.
Dialogue: 10,0:27:31.02,0:27:32.05,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 10,0:27:32.05,0:27:37.78,Default,,0,0,0,,So, friends, let’s make \N"Advance and advance again!" our motto
Dialogue: 10,0:27:37.78,0:27:41.02,Default,,0,0,0,,and win in May with flying colors!
Dialogue: 10,0:27:41.37,0:27:42.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's do it!
Dialogue: 10,0:27:42.62,0:27:44.85,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll totally win!
Dialogue: 10,0:27:45.58,0:27:50.82,NarrTop,,0,0,0,,In early May, the Abeno District \Nled all 34 districts of the Osaka Branch
Dialogue: 10,0:27:50.82,0:27:54.77,NarrTop,,0,0,0,,and held a convention \Nat Nakanoshima Public Hall,
Dialogue: 10,0:27:54.77,0:27:59.29,NarrTop,,0,0,0,,rallying 3,000 branch members and friends.
Dialogue: 10,0:27:59.29,0:28:02.10,Thought,,0,0,0,,This turnout is truly impressive. {/they did well gathering together so many members}
Dialogue: 10,0:28:02.10,0:28:06.12,Thought,,0,0,0,,To think that a single district \Ncould fill this large public hall...
Dialogue: 10,0:28:06.12,0:28:09.54,Thought,,0,0,0,,This will boost the spirits \Nof the following districts.
Dialogue: 10,0:28:09.54,0:28:12.41,Default,,0,0,0,,The lion's awake at last!
Dialogue: 10,0:28:12.41,0:28:13.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, that's right!
Dialogue: 10,0:28:13.29,0:28:14.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Exactly!
Dialogue: 10,0:28:17.78,0:28:20.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Now that the lion is awake,
Dialogue: 10,0:28:20.01,0:28:23.79,Default,,0,0,0,,I truly hope everyone, \Nwith the district chief at the helm,
Dialogue: 10,0:28:23.79,0:28:31.86,Default,,0,0,0,,unites to win every battle ahead \Nand rise as the most devoted district in Osaka.
Dialogue: 10,0:28:48.25,0:28:54.05,Thought,,0,0,0,,The great success of the Abeno district rally \Nset fire to all the other districts in Osaka.
Dialogue: 10,0:28:54.05,0:28:57.93,Thought,,0,0,0,,The battle for propagation \Nis sure to take a great leap forward now.
Dialogue: 10,0:28:58.97,0:29:02.87,Thought,,0,0,0,,But we can't be all happy about it.
Dialogue: 10,0:29:02.87,0:29:06.85,Thought,,0,0,0,,We've experienced explosive growth \Nover this March and April. {mizou / 未會有 = unprecedented, miraculous; could be "we were spreading teachings of Adbhuta Ramayana" or something; https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Adbhuta_Ramayana}
Dialogue: 10,0:29:06.85,0:29:10.02,Thought,,0,0,0,,Sure enough, that gave \Nthe demons plenty to feed on—
Dialogue: 10,0:29:10.02,0:29:12.55,Thought,,0,0,0,,they’ll be showing up before long. {この3月 4月は未會有の弘教がなされた 魔の働きもいよいよ勢いを増して必ず現れてくるに違いない}
Dialogue: 10,0:29:13.21,0:29:16.76,Thought,,0,0,0,,The scriptures teach that when your faith deepens, the three obstacles
Dialogue: 10,0:29:16.76,0:29:20.65,Thought,,0,0,0,,and four demons will inevitably appear, \Neach scrambling to throw you off course.
Dialogue: 10,0:29:20.65,0:29:22.44,Thought,,0,0,0,,With the battle reaching this stage,
Dialogue: 10,0:29:22.44,0:29:25.51,Thought,,0,0,0,,the three obstacles and four demons \Nwill soon come knocking.
Dialogue: 10,0:29:25.51,0:29:27.00,Thought,,0,0,0,,I know they will!
Dialogue: 10,0:29:27.00,0:29:32.80,Thought,,0,0,0,,And I need to sound the alarm now so that \Nno one is caught by surprise when they do.
Dialogue: 10,0:29:33.59,0:29:38.31,Thought,,0,0,0,,I will include that in my talk \Nat tomorrow's HQ meeting.
Dialogue: 10,0:29:38.31,0:29:41.26,Narrator,,0,0,0,,The further Soka Gakkai advances the Common Path,
Dialogue: 10,0:29:41.26,0:29:47.69,Narrator,,0,0,0,,the more likely power-hungry \Ndemons are to surface to take advantage of them.
Dialogue: 10,0:29:48.83,0:29:54.87,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Back then, only Yamamoto Shinichi had an inkling that his prediction
Dialogue: 10,0:29:54.87,0:29:59.26,Narrator,,0,0,0,,would come true all too precisely in May.
